LORE kowloon-criminal
FLAGS KOWLOON CRIMINAL
- Jade Eels: embedded in Harbor Syndic operations; believed to hold a Syndic
  seat; three investigations closed without result; the fourth investigator
  resigned; working against them requires a very careful approach
- Violet-marked night markets operate under sanctioned ambiguity; what is sold
  there is legal; where it came from is not discussed
- Ash Cult cells throughout the city; they sabotage floodworks; they have
  popular support in lower wards; do not underestimate their infrastructure
- Salt Court Exiles (Duchess Yuen Ahi): debt rings in the southern quarter;
  exploit founding-house legal flaw in merger documentation; they employ muscle
  and need deniable contractors; they pay well but their problems follow you
- The Black Ledger — Kowloon's unredacted founding census including Conclave
  transfer names — may be in the undercity cisterns; every faction wants it
  found or buried; the finder's options are limited by who finds out first
~
